Package: poll4pop
Title: Functions for modelling central-place foraging pollinators 
Version: 1.1.1
Authors@R: as.person(c(
	"Yann Clough <yann.clough@cec.lu.se> [aut, cre]", 
	"Emma Gardner <e.l.gardner@reading.ac.uk> [aut]",
	"Johanna Haeussler <johanna.haeussler@idiv.de> [aut]",
	"Charlotte Baey <charlotte.baey@univ-lille.fr> [aut]",
	"Ullrika Sahlin <ullrika.sahlin@cec.lu.se> [aut]",
	"Henrik G. Smith <henrik.smith@biol.lu.se> [aut]"
  ))
Description: Collection of functions for spatially-explicit modelling of central-place foraging pollinators (bumble bees, solitary bees etc.).
	Uses spatial data on floral and nesting quality to compute flower visitation and population dynamics for wild pollinators for a given year.
	Can be used for multiple years by running a loop and using as input the output of the previous model.
